The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Arpit scores century
                                                                                                                                   Arpit scores century
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Saurashtra batsman Arpit Vasavada scored 102 as the visitors scored 223 for seven against Bengal at stumps on the first day of the CK Nayudu Trophy match being played at the Jadavpur University, Salt Lake campus. Arpit faced 170 deliveries and hit 12 boundaries.         
	He was caught by Sreevats Goswami, off Sami Ahmed.         
	Brief scores         
	Saurashtra 223/7 (A. Vasavada 102, P. Solanki 52, Md Ashrafuddin 3/42) vs Bengal. Match to continue.                                                                                                                       
